<plot>Flush with first love, two teenagers cut school to spend the day together in the outskirts of their suburban New Jersey community. But what begins as an experiment in earnest rule-breaking and youthful romance deteriorates into an exercise in disillusionment. Atmospheric and closely observed, All Day Long is a bittersweet portrait of the frustrations of adolescence and the persistent unwillingness of reality to meet expectations.</plot><url>http://localhost:8983/solr/movie.html?030622</url></doc>
